You are working inside a guarded fullstack platform.

Stack:
- Backend: FastAPI + Pydantic + Mongo ODM
- Frontend: React + Vite + Tailwind + Zustand + React Query

Rules:
- Do NOT introduce new frameworks or libraries.
- Do NOT modify docker-compose unless asked.
- Backend APIs must go in backend/app/modules/.
- Shared backend logic goes in backend/app/services/.
- UI components must go in frontend/src/components/ui/.
- Pages go in frontend/src/pages/.
- Do NOT write inline CSS. Use Tailwind utility classes.
- Do NOT bypass Auth or RBAC checks.
- Do NOT create new databases.
- Follow existing naming conventions.
- If unsure, ask before changing structure.

Design System Rules:
- Always use design system components from frontend/src/components/ui/.
- Never write raw HTML <input> or <button> elements outside ui components.
- Use the Button component for all buttons.
- Use the Input component for all text inputs.
- Use the Card component for content containers.
- Landing pages must use design-system components.
- Tailwind tokens come from design-system/design-tokens.css.
- Never define colors inline. Use CSS variables like var(--btn-primary-bg).

App Personalization:
    - system.config.json is the source of truth for app name, description, theme color, slug, and layout.
- Docker service names must reference values in system.config.json (e.g., <slug>-backend).
- The frontend reads config from /system.config.json (served from public/).
- Use the useSystemConfig() hook to access system configuration in React components.

File Locations:
- Design tokens: frontend/src/design-system/design-tokens.css
- Design docs: frontend/src/design-system/design-system.md
- UI components: frontend/src/components/ui/
- System config: system.config.json and frontend/public/system.config.json

System Rules:
- system.config.json is the single source of truth for app configuration.
- UI layout must use AppShell, Sidebar, and HeaderBar components.
- Only design-system components allowed for UI (Button, Input, Card, etc.).
- No direct color values in classnames or inline styles - use CSS variables.
- Sidebar collapsed state is persisted in localStorage.
- All form validation must mirror backend Pydantic schemas.

Layout Components:
- AppShell: Main layout wrapper with sidebar, header, and content area.
- Sidebar: Collapsible navigation with localStorage persistence.
- HeaderBar: Top navigation bar with breadcrumbs and user menu.

Verification:
- Run ./verify-project.sh to check project configuration and compliance.
- Fix any warnings or errors before deployment.

App Generation Rules:
- Use ./generate-app.sh to create new app modules.
- Never manually create files in backend/app/modules/ or frontend/src/pages/generated/.
- Generated apps must be registered in templates/generated-apps.json.
- After generation, complete the manual integration steps:
  1. Export router in backend/app/modules/__init__.py
  2. Register router in backend/app/api/api.py
  3. Add frontend routes in frontend/src/App.tsx
- Generated app templates are in templates/backend/_base/ and templates/frontend/_base/.
- Template types: saas-dashboard, marketplace, ocr-engine, analytics-platform, legal-ai, fraud-detector, automation-suite, ai-assistant.
- Frontend Zod schemas mirror backend Pydantic schemas (generated in modules/<slug>/schema.ts).
